text: Year 35 BC was either a common year starting on Thursday or Friday or a leap year starting on Wednesday, Thursday or Friday of the Julian calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Cornificius and Sextus. == Events == * Illyria becomes a Roman province * Pannonia is attacked by Octavian Caesar * Sextus Pompeius defeats Gaius Furnius * Azes I, Indo- Scythian ruler, completed the domination of the Scythians in northern India. == Births == *Mollius MacGillus Carterus == Deaths == * Aristobulus III of Judea, high priest (drowned) (b. 53 BC) * Sextus Pompeius, executed in Miletus (b. c. 67 BC) Category:30s BC
title: 35 BC
